<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-09-20T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-09-20T11:00:00-05:00" n="582" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d582">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3531/1589: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Tuck</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos
                                        Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-20T13:00:00-03:00">September 20, 1940—1
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 20—11:56 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>428. Department’s 216, September 19, 1 p.m. We presume that the
                            preliminary conversations are to be considered as strictly confidential
                            and will so inform the Foreign Office.</p>
                        <pb facs="0509" n="497" xml:id="pg_497"/>
                        <p>If at a later date, possibly when the text of the corn agreement is
                            received here, the Department should wish to give publicity to the
                            negotiations, it is urged that the Embassy be advised in advance.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Tuck</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>